  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-001">.NET 8 Minimal API + BackgroundService. SSE uses Minimal API streamed response (existing in `SprkChatAgent`).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-008">Endpoint-filter authorization on `POST /api/ai/gates/in-chat/respond`. NO global middleware.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">Feature-module DI. ≤15 total non-framework registrations in `AddActionEngineModule()`. This task adds: `IGateApprovalChannel`, its impl, the resolver, and the endpoint registration (4 slots; remaining budget tracked in `AddGatesFeature()`).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">AI Architecture (refined). BFF placement; SSE channel lives inside the AI feature module.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-015">Audit per gate decision: Tier 2 hash + Tier 3 work history. ALL terminal outcomes (Approved/Rejected/TimedOut) MUST audit.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-019">ProblemDetails (RFC 7807) for endpoint errors (e.g., unknown correlationId, malformed body).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-028">Endpoint auth via `useAuth()` / `authenticatedFetch` from client; server outbound MI not applicable (no outbound calls). Audit middleware enriches every request with `oid`, `appid`, `obo`, `tenantId`, `correlationId`.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">Publish-size delta ≤ 5 MB compressed. This task adds ≤400 LoC; expected delta &lt; 0.1 MB.</constraint>
    <constraint source="bff-extensions.md">Pre-merge checklist: placement = BFF (SSE coupling makes BFF the only valid placement); no new NuGet packages; ADRs cited.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Default for `GateType.Manual` and the Assistant playbook default per design §7.4.3.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Fail-safe semantics: SSE session closure → unresolved gates auto-Rejected with `reason: "session closed"`.</constraint>
  </constraints>

