  <steps>
    <step order="0">Context check: working tree clean, branch `work/ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1`, baseline build passes, task 030 ✅. Load knowledge. Declare RIGOR LEVEL: FULL.</step>
    <step order="1">Read task 030 contract + design §5 + §7.4. Trace `SprkChatAgent` SSE event flow to identify the right extension point for `gate.request` events without breaking existing chat consumers.</step>
    <step order="2">Create `IGateApprovalChannel.cs` — interface with `Task EmitGateRequestAsync(string sessionId, GateRequest request, CancellationToken ct)` and `Task&lt;bool&gt; ResolvePendingAsync(string correlationId, GateDecision decision, string? reason)`.</step>
    <step order="3">Create `SseGateApprovalChannel.cs` — singleton; ctor injects `ISprkChatSseDispatcher` (existing). Maintains `ConcurrentDictionary&lt;string, TaskCompletionSource&lt;GateOutcome&gt;&gt;` keyed on `correlationId`. `EmitGateRequestAsync` writes the SSE event AND registers TCS. `ResolvePendingAsync` flips the TCS. Add explicit cleanup on TCS resolution (remove from dictionary).</step>
    <step order="4">Create `InteractiveInChatGateResolver.cs` — ctor injects `IGateApprovalChannel`, `IAuditService`, `ILogger&lt;...&gt;`. `ResolveAsync`: emit SSE → await TCS with `request.TimeoutSeconds` cancellation → on completion, audit + return outcome. On timeout, audit `TimedOut` + return outcome.</step>
    <step order="5">Create `Api/Ai/GateEndpoints.cs` — `MapGateEndpoints()` registers `POST /api/ai/gates/in-chat/respond`. Body: `{ correlationId: string, decision: "Approved"|"Rejected", reason?: string }`. Endpoint calls `IGateApprovalChannel.ResolvePendingAsync`. Returns 204 on success, ProblemDetails 404 on unknown correlationId. Apply `.AddEndpointFilter&lt;AuthorizationEndpointFilter&gt;()`.</step>
    <step order="6">Wire endpoint registration via `MapGateEndpoints()` call in `EndpointMappingExtensions.cs` (alongside other AI endpoint maps).</step>
    <step order="7">Register DI in `AddGatesFeature()` (extending `AddActionEngineModule.cs`): `services.AddSingleton&lt;IGateApprovalChannel, SseGateApprovalChannel&gt;(); services.AddKeyedScoped&lt;IGateResolver, InteractiveInChatGateResolver&gt;(GateType.Manual);` — and any optional `Conditional`/playbook default routing per design §7.4.</step>
    <step order="8">Write unit tests:
      (a) `ResolveAsync_HappyPath_Approved` — emits SSE, simulates `ResolvePendingAsync(Approved)`, returns `Approved` outcome + audits.
      (b) `ResolveAsync_HappyPath_Rejected` — similar, with reason propagated.
      (c) `ResolveAsync_Timeout_AutoRejects` — TCS never resolves within timeout; outcome = `TimedOut` + audit.
      (d) `ResolvePendingAsync_DuplicateCall_IsIdempotent` — second call returns false; no double-resolve.
      (e) `ResolveAsync_AuditOrdering_AfterTerminalDecision` — audit called exactly once per terminal outcome.
      (f) Endpoint integration test: `POST /api/ai/gates/in-chat/respond` returns 204 for known correlationId; 404 ProblemDetails for unknown.</step>
    <step order="9">Build + run tests: `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` exits 0; `dotnet test` passes new tests. Measure publish-size delta; expect &lt; 0.1 MB. Record in `notes/measurements/032-publish-size-delta.md`.</step>
    <step order="9.5">Run quality gates: `code-review` (TCS lifecycle correctness — no leaks; SSE event vocabulary correctness; audit ordering), `adr-check` (ADR-001/008/010/013/015/019/028/029).</step>
    <step order="10">Update `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`: 032 ✅. Update `current-task.md`.</step>
    <step order="11">Commit + push. Document SSE event vocabulary additions in `notes/decisions/032-sse-gate-events.md` so task 036 (GateApprovalCard) knows the event shape.</step>
  </steps>

