  <notes>
    The `IGateApprovalChannel` abstraction is intentional — task 036 (`GateApprovalCard` UI) consumes the SSE event vocabulary; task 035 (timeout sweep) calls `ResolvePendingAsync` with `TimedOut` decision. Both downstream consumers see a stable interface.

    Singleton lifetime for `SseGateApprovalChannel` is required because the pending-TCS dictionary spans requests (the gate request comes from one HTTP call; the resolution arrives on a different HTTP call). Scoped lifetime would lose state.

    Session-close handling: out of scope for this task — the orchestrator (Phase 4) signals session closure; this resolver only needs to cooperate by exposing a `CancelAllForSessionAsync(sessionId)` method on the channel. Stub it now if straightforward; otherwise document a TODO in `notes/decisions/032-sse-gate-events.md`.
  </notes>

